: \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After three Olympics, it was dropped, then reinstated at the 2020 Tokyo Games when the event was held for men and women.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three Olympics\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The UCI has included the men's Madison at the Track World Championships since 1995, while the women have competed for the rainbow jersey since 2016.\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1042, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999999736310204, \"rank\": 2.6368870233864646e-08, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}, {\"begin\": 1069, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.907904072278942, \"rank\": 0.1014379498153773, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Track World Championships\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1109}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"the rainbow jersey\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1174}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A winning Madison team is determined by points rather than time, and these points are amassed over 200 laps (50 kilometres).\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1198, \"end\": 1205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.907904072278942, \"rank\": 0.1014379498153773, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"these points\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"over 200 laps\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"50 kilometres\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sprints are contested every 10 laps, with the top four teams rewarded, and the final lap offers double points.\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1423, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sprints\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1320}, {\"ngram\": \"every 10 laps\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1348}, {\"ngram\": \"the top four teams\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"the final lap\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"double points\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1422}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tactics come into play when a team tries to lap the field, which earns 20 bonus points, and any team that gets lapped then has 20 points deducted.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1571, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tactics\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1447}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"20 bonus points\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"any team\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"20 points\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the spectators seem to respond the most to the sequence of choreographed relay exchanges between teammates.\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the spectators\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1591}, {\"ngram\": \"the sequence\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1632}, {\"ngram\": \"choreographed relay exchanges\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1665}, {\"ngram\": \"teammates\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each rider takes a turn being \\\"active\\\" on the track, while the other is \\\"inactive\\\" and coasts while waiting for a relay swap, which can be made at any time.\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1841, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each rider\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"a turn\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1708}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"a relay swap\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1809}, {\"ngram\": \"any time\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many exchanges are made by teammates gripping hands and then launching one rider forward with a 'handsling' motion.\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1957, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many exchanges\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1856}, {\"ngram\": \"teammates\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"hands\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1893}, {\"ngram\": \"one rider\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1922}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'handsling' motion\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 1956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Netherlands is the reigning world champion in the men's Madison, and the winning pair of Jan Willem van Schip and Yoeri Havik are the favourites for gold in Paris.\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.7248104849520967, \"rank\": 0.37761256110486513, \"text\": \"The Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2019, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.907904072278942, \"rank\": 0.1014379498153773, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"type